Prosper Loan Data Exploration.¶

by Teslim Kehinde.¶

Introduction¶

This data set contains 113,937 loans with 81 variables on each loan, including loan amount, borrower rate (or interest rate), current loan status, borrower income, and many others.

# Convert Term, LoanStatus, Income range to categorical datatype
ordinal_var_diction = {'Term': [12, 36, 60],
                    'LoanStatus': ['Completed', 'FinalPaymentInProgress', 'Current', 'Defaulted', 'Chargedoff',                                   'Past Due (1-15 days)', 'Past Due (16-30 days)', 'Past Due (61-90 days)',
                                   'Past Due (31-60 days)', 'Past Due (91-120 days)', 'Past Due (>120 days)'],
                    'IncomeRange': ['Not displayed', 'Not employed', '$0', '$1-24,999', '$25,000-49,999', '$50,000-74,999',
                                    '$75,000-99,999', '$100,000+']}

for variable in ordinal_var_diction:
    ordered_variable = pd.api.types.CategoricalDtype(ordered = True, categories = ordinal_var_diction[variable])
    n_loan[variable] = n_loan[variable].astype(ordered_variable)

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

There are 113,937 loans in the dataset with 81 variables, shortened to 30 variables, dropping columns with Nan values. Most variables are numeric in nature, but the variables Term, LoanStatus, Income range are ordered factor variables.

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

What factors affects a loan outcome status. What affects the borrowers interest rate

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

I expect that the Income Range would have more effect on the Loan Status. The higher the income range the bettter the loan status. I will also consider other variables in this exploration, e.g Term, LoanStatus, BorrowerRate, LenderYield, ListingCategory (numeric), IsBorrowerHomeowner, IncomeRange, StatedMonthlyIncome, LoanNumber, Loan Origination date, Listing Creation Date.

Univariate Exploration¶

I'll start by looking at the distribution on the main variable of interest: Loan Status.

    sb.boxplot(x=x, y=y, color=default_color)
    plt.xticks(rotation = 90)

Conclusions¶

In this process of analysing the prosper dataset, I looked out to determining the factors that afffects the Loan status of the data, by first visualizing each single variable, including the variable of interest, and also performing a bivariate and multivariate visualization on the variables.

I noticed that the nature of the terms of loans that are completed are Intermediate, i.e 36 months.

Also noticed that abandoned loans are 60 months in nature.

In the process of exploration, i noticed that income range of people with 50,000 - 74,999, have there payment to be up to date, while those with income range around 25,000 - 49,999 are completed.

Thus it is okay to deduce that the term of the loans and the Income Range of the borrowers affects the Loan Status.
